# Students

The Students page is the central hub for managing all student records in your school. School administrators and staff use this page to register new students, view and edit student profiles, track admission status, and access student documents and history. Every student in your school appears here with their complete information.

---

## Page Overview

When you open the Students page, you will see:

### Summary Cards

- **Total Students** — The total number of students registered across your organization, regardless of status.
- **Male** — Count of registered male students.
- **Female** — Count of registered female students.
- **Orphans** — Students marked as orphans who may need special care or fee waivers.

### Filters & Search

- **Search** — Search by student name, admission number, father name, guardian phone, or card number. Type at least 2 characters to start searching.
- **School** — Filter students by a specific school (if your organization has multiple schools). Default is "All Schools".
- **Status** — Filter by student status: All Status, Applied, Admitted, Active, or Withdrawn.
- **Gender** — Filter by gender: All Genders, Male, or Female.

---

## Data Table

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| Picture | Student photo thumbnail (60px). Shows a default avatar if no picture uploaded. |
| Admission # | The unique admission number assigned to the student. Hidden on mobile screens. |
| Student | Full name with status badge (colored), orphan badge if applicable, father name, and guardian phone below. |
| School | The school the student belongs to. Hidden on mobile and tablet. |
| Gender | Gender badge (Male/Female). Hidden on mobile and tablet. |
| Applying Grade | The grade/class the student is applying for. Hidden on mobile and tablet. |
| Actions | Dropdown menu with row-level actions. |

### Row Actions

When you click the actions menu (⋮) on any student row:

- **View Profile** — Opens a dialog showing the student's complete profile information including personal details, address, guardian info, and additional notes.
- **Print Profile** — Generates a PDF of the student's profile that you can print or save.
- **Documents** — Opens a dialog where you can upload, view, and manage student documents (certificates, ID copies, etc.).
- **Educational History** — Opens a dialog showing the student's previous school records and educational background.
- **Discipline Records** — Opens a dialog to view and add discipline records for the student.
- **Fee Assignments** — Navigates to the student's fee assignment page where you can see and manage their fee structure.
- **View History** — Navigates to the student's complete history page with timeline, attendance, exams, and fees.
- **Edit** — Opens the student edit form with all current data pre-filled.
- **Delete** — Shows a confirmation dialog. Deleting a student removes their record permanently.

---

## Registering a New Student

To register a new student, click the **"Register Student"** button at the top-right of the page. A multi-tab form will open:

### Tab 1: Admission Information

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| School | Dropdown | Auto | Automatically selected if your organization has only one school. Choose manually if multiple schools exist. |
| Admission No | Text | Yes | A unique admission number for the student. Must not duplicate an existing number. |
| Card Number | Text | No | Optional ID card number for the student. |
| Applying Grade | Dropdown | No | The grade/class the student is applying for. |
| Admission Year | Text | No | The year of admission (e.g., 1403). |

### Tab 2: Personal Information

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| Full Name | Text (autocomplete) | Yes | The student's full name. Autocomplete suggests existing names to help avoid duplicates. |
| Father Name | Text (autocomplete) | Yes | Father's full name. |
| Tazkira Number | Text | No | National ID (Tazkira) number. |
| Phone | Text | No | Student's phone number. |
| Grandfather Name | Text (autocomplete) | No | Grandfather's name. |
| Gender | Select | Yes | Male or Female. |
| Birth Year | Text (auto) | No | Auto-calculated from Birth Date if provided. |
| Birth Date | Date Picker | No | Student's date of birth. Selecting this auto-fills Birth Year and Age. |
| Age | Text (auto) | No | Auto-calculated from Birth Date. |
| Preferred Language | Select | No | Student's preferred language. |
| Nationality | Text | No | Student's nationality. |
| Previous School | Text | No | Name of the student's previous school. |

{...continues for all tabs...}

### What Happens After Submission

1. The system checks for duplicate students (matching name + father name).
2. If a duplicate is found, you'll see a warning and can choose to proceed or cancel.
3. The system checks your subscription limit — if you've reached the maximum students, registration is blocked.
4. On success, a "Student registered successfully" message appears.
5. If a picture was uploaded, it's saved to the student's profile.
6. The form closes and the student table refreshes to show the new student.

